# Installation instructions
Working on Ubuntu via WSL
Install Ubuntu via WSL (Windows 10/11)
1. Open PowerShell as Administrator
2. Install WSL + Ubuntu in One Command
wsl --install
3. Wait for Ubuntu to Launch - linux username, password
4. Verify Everything Works
lsb_release -a
output:
Distributor ID: Ubuntu
Release:        22.04


5. Install Docker (Locally)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

6. restart unbuntu

7. To Confirm Itâ€™s Running in ubuntu:
docker info
output:
Server:
 Containers: ...
 Server Version: ...
 Storage Driver: ...

8. Installed Docker Directly in Ubuntu (without Docker Desktop)
1: Create Your Project Folder
mkdir ~/cloud-app && cd ~/cloud-app

2: Create docker-compose.yml
These services include:
A PostgreSQL database
A FastApi backend (Python API)
A React frontend
An NGINX reverse proxy to route web traffic
Monitoring tools: Prometheus, Grafana, and cAdvisor
Adminer: a web UI for your database



